<h2 class="virus">Virus Info:</h2>
<p class="virus">Covid-19 is a a particular strain of coronaviruses. It was discovered in December of 2019 in the Wuhan region of China, and since then it has infected
    millions around the world. It is a respiratory illness which causes symptoms ranging from a light cough to severe pneumonia. Although no cure exists for the virus, there are ways to curb the spread of the disease through
    face-masks, self-isolation, and social distancing. The creation of multiple working vaccines provided the world with hope and a pathway towards a Covid-19 free future.
<br>
